<p>When users add a table in my CMS the table is set to 100% width thanks to this TinyMCE configuration:</p>  <pre><code>tinymce.init({table_default_styles : {width:'100%'}}); </code></pre>  <p>When they resize the table with the handle bars, the table gets a fixed width in pixels instead of percentages. How can i configure the use of percentages (instead of pixels) while resizing the table?</p>